  <summary>7/10/2001--Introduced.
Law Enforcement Memorial Act - Authorizes the Attorney General to make grants for up to 50 percent of the total cost of a program to States, units of local government, and Indian tribes to carry out programs to construct memorials to honor men and women of the United States who were killed or disabled while serving as law enforcement or public safety officers.</summary>
